# `a2a whatsnew`: renders the embedded release-notes corpus — no space, no
# config needed. This shared t3 test binary is built with -X
# main.version=0.1.0 (main_test.go), which predates every entry in the real
# corpus (0.2.0/0.3.0/0.4.0) — so every invocation below exercises the
# documented empty-result paths (upto=binaryVersion bounds --since; no
# Exactly(binaryVersion) match for the bare form) deterministically, rather
# than positive digest content. Rich rendering (digest text, impact
# ordering, action-scope directives, JSON shape) is covered by
# internal/cli/cmd_whatsnew_test.go and internal/mcp/tools_whatsnew_test.go
# against a fixed, injected corpus.
exec a2a whatsnew
stdout 'no release notes for version 0\.1\.0'

exec a2a whatsnew --since 0.1.0
stdout 'no release notes since 0\.1\.0'

exec a2a whatsnew --since 0.1.0 --json
stdout '\[\]'
